						               													<description>Based on a traditional outdoor game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Long donkey players are divided into two teams. Each team has 4 pawns and one donkey with 8 card slots. Each card slot on the donkeys is divided into two parts: The defense area and the attack area.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The pawns of each team are &amp;ldquo;climbing&amp;rdquo; on the attack area of the opposite&amp;rsquo;s team donkey based on their jump cards. The other team must put a defense card on their donkey&amp;rsquo;s defense area.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every slot of a team&amp;rsquo;s donkey has 1 stamina value by default. &amp;#10;Every single pawn burdens a slot of the opposite team&amp;rsquo;s donkey by 1 weight value. No defense card needed on that slot by the defending team.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every 2 pawns burden a slot of the opposite team&amp;rsquo;s donkey by 4 weight value. The defending team needs at least a +4 defense card on that slot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every 3 pawns burden a slot of the opposite team&amp;rsquo;s donkey by 9 weight value. The defending team needs at least a +8 defense card on that slot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every 4 pawns burden a slot of the opposite team&amp;rsquo;s donkey by 16 weight value. The defending team needs at least the +2 +6 +8 defense cards on that slot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The end of the game:&amp;#10;When there is less stamina value than the opponent&amp;rsquo;s weight value on a single slot of a donkey at the end of the turn, the attacking team wins the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
